UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1864
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION designating the Barry Barrett Memorial Bridge in
2 Marshall County.
3 WHEREAS, Barry Shane Barrett was born on December 19, 1972, to parents David
4 Lee Barrett and Sandra Adair Barrett; and
5 WHEREAS, Barry Barrett founded, operated, and built Barry Barrett Trucking
6 LLC, and was a faithful member of and deacon for the congregation of Zion Cause
7 Baptist Church; and
8 WHEREAS, Barry Barrett took great pride and joy in his community and the
9 Commonwealth. From serving his local community in Marshall County, to watching the
10 University of Kentucky Wildcats play basketball, he found much joy in life through the
11 culture of Kentucky; and
12 WHEREAS, Barry Barrett is survived by his dear wife Missy Ann Barrett; his son
13 Shane (Katherine) Barrett; his daughter Samantha (Joseph) Scholl; and grandchildren MJ
14 Barrett and Evie Kate Barrett; and
15 WHEREAS, the people of Marshall County consider Barry Barrett to have been an
16 honorable man, faithful leader, and generous soul, and wish to ensure he is recognized for
17 his service and graciousness to the community;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
20 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate the bridge on Kentucky
21 Route 2595 corssing Cypress Creek (Bridge ID #079B00142N) in Marshall County as the
22 "Barry Barrett Memorial Bridge" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this
23 Resolution, erect appropriate signage denoting this designation.
